+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Genesis Framework is the WordPress framework to know. In this course, you'll learn about looking for child themes, looking for Genesis-specific plugins, and checking out its theme settings. Then we will discuss how to pick a child theme to meet a site's needs, gathering tools to setup a child theme for modification, and some really quick mods that include dashboard changes. Finally, using common plugins, SFTP editing some CSS code and a couple PHP functions that are readily available from StudioPress.com, we will encourage you to try new configurations to be unique rather than "cookie-cutter Genesis.
